         <div type="translation">
            <p>Plotia Helen[a], freedwoman of Aulus and of a woman, (made this) for herself,
               and for Aulus Plotius Lucrio, (her) deserving husband, and for Gaius Hostius
               Primigenitus, Aulus Plotius Felix, freedman, Plotia Veneria, freedwoman, Aulus
               Plotius Crescens, freedman, and for the[ir] descendants.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 3: a potio; 
                      line 6: hostio felici (Dennison). Line 3: viro [bene]; line 5: Primigeni[o et]; line 6: liber[to et]; line 9: eoru[m] (AE).</p>
         </div>
